                     width="16">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd"
                          d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path>
                </svg>
            </a>Collation Support
        </h2>
        <p>This adapter includes support for <a
                    href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/release-notes/3.4/#collation-and-case-insensitive-indexes"
                    rel="nofollow">collation and case insensitive indexes available in MongoDB v3.4</a>. Collation
            parameters may be passed using the special <code>collation</code> parameter to the <code>find()</code>,
            <code>remove()</code> and <code>patch()</code> methods.</p>
        <h3><a href="#example-patch-records-with-case-insensitive-alphabetical-ordering" aria-hidden="true"
               class="anchor" id="user-content-example-patch-records-with-case-insensitive-alphabetical-ordering">
                <svg aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16"
